<paragraph blockId="17.[1060,1219,1860,1884]" box="[1060,1219,1860,1884]" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">
<figureCitation box="[1060,1219,1860,1884]" captionStart="Text-fig" captionStartId="19.[125,206,1904,1925]" captionTargetBox="[128,1438,151,1884]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Text-fig. 11. Scanning electron microscope (SEM) images of seeds assigned to the BEG group (a–d) and associated pollen grains (e–i); Torres Vedras locality, Portugal. a) Seed of Tomcatia taylorii showing the four horns formed by extensions of the envelope and the central projection of the envelope that surrounds to the micropylar tube; b, c) Seeds of Quadrispermum parvum in lateral (b) and apical (c) views showing the transverse ribs and the central projection of the envelope that surrounds the micropylar tube; d–f) Seeds of Ephedrispermum lusitanicum showing the four-angled seed envelope (d), the micropylar tube surrounded by the tissues of the integument (e), and ephedroid pollen grains on the seed surface (f); g) Apex of seed of Quadrispermum parvum showing simple" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5386239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5386239/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">Text-fig. 11d–f</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
